From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: SuperKali <hello@superkali.me>
Date: Sat, 18 Jul 2026 03:10:00 +0200
Subject: drm/msm/dp: do not fail audio prepare when the port is off

msm_dp_audio_prepare() returns -EINVAL when the DP link is off. With the
generic HDMI codec the ALSA card is always present, so userspace can open
the DP PCM and call prepare() while the port is disconnected. The -EINVAL
aborts hw_params and UCM setup, leaving a dummy sink even once a monitor
is connected. The clocks are gated while the port is off, so there is
nothing to program: return success. Audio is set up from the plug path
when the link comes up.

Signed-off-by: SuperKali <hello@superkali.me>
---
 drivers/gpu/drm/msm/dp/dp_audio.c | 16 ++++------
 1 file changed, 6 insertions(+), 10 deletions(-)

diff --git a/drivers/gpu/drm/msm/dp/dp_audio.c b/drivers/gpu/drm/msm/dp/dp_audio.c
index 111111111111..222222222222 100644
--- a/drivers/gpu/drm/msm/dp/dp_audio.c
+++ b/drivers/gpu/drm/msm/dp/dp_audio.c
@@ -277,17 +277,13 @@ int msm_dp_audio_prepare(struct drm_bridge *bridge,
 	msm_dp_display = to_dp_bridge(bridge)->msm_dp_display;
 
 	/*
-	 * there could be cases where sound card can be opened even
-	 * before OR even when DP is not connected . This can cause
-	 * unclocked access as the audio subsystem relies on the DP
-	 * driver to maintain the correct state of clocks. To protect
-	 * such cases check for connection status and bail out if not
-	 * connected.
+	 * Userspace can probe the DP PCMs while the connector is unplugged or
+	 * disabled. The controller clocks are off then, so skip the register
+	 * programming instead of failing, the jack and ELD state still report
+	 * sink availability.
 	 */
-	if (!msm_dp_display->power_on) {
-		rc = -EINVAL;
-		goto end;
-	}
+	if (!msm_dp_display->power_on)
+		return 0;
 
 	audio = msm_dp_audio_get_data(msm_dp_display);
 	if (IS_ERR(audio)) {
